psidev.psi.mi.jami.enricher.listener.impl

Class EnricherListenerManager<O,T extends EnricherListener<O>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • psidev.psi.mi.jami.enricher.listener.impl.EnricherListenerManager<O,T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - The type of the listeners which are to be used.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    EnricherListener<O>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    CvTermEnricherListenerManager, EntityEnricherListenerManager, ExperimentEnricherListenerManager, FeatureEnricherListenerManager, InteractionEnricherListenerManager, InteractorEnricherListenerManager, OrganismEnricherListenerManager, PublicationEnricherListenerManager

    public abstract class EnricherListenerManager<O,T extends EnricherListener<O>>
extends Object
implements EnricherListener<O>
    A manager for listeners which holds a list of listeners. Listener manager allows enrichers to send events to multiple listeners. A listener itself, it implements all methods which will then fire the corresponding method in each entry of the listener list. No promise can be given to the order in which the listeners are fired.
    Since:
    08/07/13
    Author:
    Gabriel Aldam (galdam@ebi.ac.uk)
